            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2012-10-17 17:48:18 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Adding an info message if the compile cache&#39;s file count is below a certain 
threshold. I made this threshold 1,000, which is actually below the number of 
files in a new cache after compiling a Desktop skeleton (it&#39;s more like 1,500) 
files. These are mostly related to framework classes, so any slightly more 
complicated application than such a skeleton will have more framework classes 
in the cache. So the cache will certainly not be saturated with information 
about framework classes if you are below this threshold, and compilation of the 
application will be delayed by this.

75895c2 (master)</thetext>
